cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.SE

This paper focuses on the performance tuning of BLAS and LAPACK, which are fundamental building blocks for High Performance Computing (HPC) applications. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of the Floating Point Unit (FPU) micro-architecture on the performance of BLAS and LAPACK, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.PF (Performance) sub-category. The paper also involves theoretical analysis and characterization of BLAS and LAPACK, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a design of a Processing Element (PE) and compares its performance with recent custom realizations of BLAS and LAPACK, which could make it relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
